- Milestone 4 is implemented and automatically validated, so the review's
  pre-milestone-4 absence list and “reported” type descriptions are stale.
  Visible user acceptance is still outstanding and remains the milestone-5
  sequencing gate.
- The implemented spatial contract is
  `application.working_grid.WorkingGridSettings` plus
  `ResolvedWorkingGrid`. Concrete resolved fields are `work_width`,
  `work_height`, `resolved_block_size`, `rows`, and `columns`; the handoff's
  illustrative `working_width`, `working_height`, and
  `block_size_working_px` names do not exist.
- `IsolateTab` owns session-local grid intent and its current immutable
  resolution. Requested downsample and block intent survive asset switches and
  re-resolve against each new registered extent; application restart resets to
  `1.0` and auto. `IsolateSession` remains the temporal player/media owner and
  provides `snapshot_working_window_request()`.
- A future compute action should capture the temporal request and current
  resolved grid together. When the source opens, it must compare
  `ResolvedWorkingWindow.width,height` with
  `ResolvedWorkingGrid.source_width,source_height` before consuming pixels.
- `FrameBatch` exposes shape `(batch, height, width, 3)`. Its buffers are
  immutable exact-sized `bytes` from `MediaSession.read_frame_rgb`, tightly
  packed in row-major RGB order with pixel stride 3 and row stride
  `width * 3`. Short frames raise a structured decode failure; no padding or
  approximate reshape exists.
- The source plane is native-resolution decoded `rgb24`, not source-native
  luma. `PlaneDescriptor` records FFmpeg, source pixel format, color range,
  color space, transfer, and primaries, but the current source contract does
  not establish a canonical source encoded-luma plane or fully pin FFmpeg's
  conversion implementation/version.
- The smallest honest milestone-5 representation is therefore the review's
  path B: a distinctly named post-decoder Rec.601-like weighted RGB intensity.
  Its result must retain the accepted plane descriptor and backend provenance
  and must not claim canonical/source-native luma.
- `WorkingWindowStream` already checks cancellation before each frame read and
  owns one final `COMPLETE`, `CANCELLED`, `TRUNCATED`, or `FAILED` outcome.
  Normal completion, cancellation, failure, explicit close, and context exit
  close the request-local session. A channel should embed this exact outcome
  and separately record only channel-stage outcome and actually reduced span.
- `open_working_window(...)` constructs the request-local `MediaSession`
  immediately. Exact retained-result admission therefore has to use the
  captured span and grid to reject over-budget work before calling it.
- Decision 003 now establishes available compute resources and execution policy
  as first-class product concepts. It does not supply the initial numeric
  in-memory result budget; milestone 5 must define that value/default and accept
  it through a portable Qt-free resource-policy seam rather than silently
  inventing an intensity-specific limit.
- There is no scientific worker/supersession seam yet. The existing
  `IsolateDecodeThread` is a display worker around a shared session; its stop
  path interrupts cross-thread, waits up to three seconds without checking the
  return value, then drops the decoder reference. Milestone 5 must not copy
  that lifecycle.
- The safe new-worker boundary is: GUI owns cancellation/token/pending request;
  worker checks cancellation before creating, then exclusively creates,
  consumes, and closes its request-local stream; worker emits one terminal
  outcome only after close; GUI starts a pending replacement only after
  verified thread exit and retains ownership on cleanup failure.
- `IsolateSession.state_changed` exposes current-frame changes, and
  `timeline_seek`/`timeline_scrub` provide seek paths. The right-hand channel
  area is still the explicit `No channels added yet.` placeholder. No channel
  cursor signal, result owner, or panel is implemented.
- There is no current channel behavior that conflicts with the fixed
  conversion/downsample/block/publication rules because no channel exists.
  There is also no NumPy or OpenCV project dependency, so no vectorized or
  backend area reducer may be assumed before implementation.
